# Testing (HalalScan)

Full guide: [TESTING.md](../../TESTING.md) (UI E2E, integration, OCR, fixtures).

## CI test command

```bash
flutter test test/services/ test/constants/ test/models/ test/config_test.dart
```

Run this after behavior changes in `lib/` or `test/`.

## What to test

- Real behavior (lookup pipeline, keyword override, cache TTL, parsing) — not implementation trivia.
- Mirror patterns in `test/services/` (mocks, fixtures under `test_data/` where relevant).
- Do not add tests that only assert obvious truths or duplicate the implementation line-for-line.

## Fixtures

- Offline product fixtures: `test_data/` and `halal_test.db` (debug); seed via `test_data/seed_barcodes.txt` per `CLAUDE.md`.

## UI E2E (no widget mocks)

- After navigation / scan / result UI changes: local Supabase + `.\run_ui_e2e_test.ps1` (`dart_defines.e2e.json`). See [TESTING.md](../../TESTING.md#local-supabase-for-e2e).
